00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,000
Henry, do you like the first puzzle?  

180
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:07,520
Isn't it cool? Cool and wicked. The clock has 
started to tick. Hurry, hurry, hurry! BFN :-)

181
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,440
Mr Williams didn't understand anything.  

182
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:17,200
He looked at Belinda, who was still crying. 
"Belinda, please, stop crying for just one minute  

183
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:21,920
and call Mike. Tell him to come 
here at once. We need his help."

184
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,800
She looked at him in amazement and replied,  

185
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:31,840
"But Mr Williams, you sacked Mike 
about an hour ago. Don't you remember?"

186
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:36,720
Yes, now he did remember. 
There was no one to help him.

187
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:44,320
His headache was getting worse. He couldn't think. 
Then Belinda's voice came from behind his chair.  

188
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:49,760
"Why don't you call your son, Robbie? 
He's very good with computers, isn't he?"

189
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:55,440
Mr Williams got up and hugged her. "Yes! Belinda, 
you're fantastic. Why didn't I think of that?"  

190
00:17:56,640 --> 00:18:00,960
It was a school holiday so Robbie would be in his 
bedroom, playing on the computer and listening  

191
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:06,160
to music but definitely not studying. It was 
rare to see an open textbook in that bedroom.  

192
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:12,000
There were two things Mr Williams always 
associated with his son - his mobile phone  

193
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:17,120
and his baseball cap. Mr Williams picked 
up the phone and dialled his home number.

194
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:25,520
"Robbie? This is your father. Listen, I have 
a problem with the computers at the bank.  

195
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:32,560
Can you come and help me? I don't care if you're 
fighting Lara Croft. This is really important.  

196
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,400
Come as soon as possible please. Thank you."

197
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:43,280
Mr Williams put down the phone and smiled. "That 
was a great idea of yours, Belinda. Robbie's  

198
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:48,080
a teenager so I'm sure he'll understand all the 
strange symbols and abbreviations in the puzzle."

199
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:53,280
Belinda blushed. "If I could make 
another suggestion, Mr Williams?  

200
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:57,680
I think you can see where the e-mail 
